    • Method Detail

      • expandNode

        public final Tuple<List<Node>,List<Link>> expandNode(Id<Node> nodeId,
                                                     List<NetworkExpandNode.TurnInfo> turns)
        Expands the specified node that is part of the network and adds turning restrictions/maneuvers to it.

        It is done in the following way:

        1. creates for each in- and out-link a new node with
          • new_nodeId = nodeId+"-"+index; index=[0..#incidentLinks]
          • new_coord with distance r to the given node in direction of the corresponding incident Link of the given node with offset e.
           
 <-----12------         <----21-------

            x-0 o     o 1-5
                   O nodeId = x
            x-1 o     o x-4
             x-2 o   o x-3
 ------11----->         -----22------>
               |       ^
               |       |
              32       31
               |       |
               |       |
               v       |
        2. connects each incident link of the given node with the corresponding new_node 
           
 <-----12------ o     o <----21-------
                   O
 ------11-----> o     o -----22------>
                 o   o
                 |   ^
                 |   |
                32   31
                 |   |
                 |   |
                 v   |
        3. removes the given node from the network 
           
 <-----12------ o     o <----21-------

 ------11-----> o     o -----22------>
                 o   o
                 |   ^
                 |   |
                32   31
                 |   |
                 |   |
                 v   |
        4. inter-connects the new_nodes with new links as defined in the turns list, with:
          • new_linkId = fromLinkId+"-"+index; index=[0..#turn-tuples]
          • length equals the Euclidean distance
          • freespeed, capacity, permlanes, origId and type are equals to the attributes of the fromLink.
           
 <-----12------ o <--21-0-- o <----21-------

 ------11-----> o --11-1--> o -----22------>
                 \         ^
              11-2\       /31-3
                   \     /
                    v   /
                    o   o
                    |   ^
                    |   |
                   32   31
                    |   |
                    |   |
                    v   |

        Parameters:
        nodeId - the Id of the Node to expand
        turns - The List of allowed turns at the given node.
        Returns:
        The Tuple of lists containing the newly created nodes and links.

      • turnsAreSameAsSingleNode

        public boolean turnsAreSameAsSingleNode(Id<Node> nodeId,
                                        List<NetworkExpandNode.TurnInfo> turns,
                                        boolean ignoreUTurns)
        Checks whether it makes sense to expand the node with turning links or not. For example, it might not make sense to expand the node if no real restrictions are given, but just all possible options are listed -- the exact same turning options could be available without expanding the node. Thus, it usually only makes sense to expand a node if turnsAreSameAsSingleNode(Id, List, boolean) returns false. The algorithm can optionally ignore u-turns, that means that it is not checked if all u-turns are allowed according to the given turning options.
        Parameters:
        nodeId -
        turns - the allowed turning options
        ignoreUTurns - set this to true if u-turns are excluded from the check
        Returns:
        true if the list of explicit turns given results in the same turning options available as when the node is not expanded, false otherwise.
